"Joker" is "poker" with a "J"!

278
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,430
Coincidence?

279
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:49,920
That's "joincidence" with a "C"!

280
00:11:54,620 --> 00:11:55,760
Look!

281
00:11:55,810 --> 00:11:58,100
Ugly Naked Guy lit a bunch of candles.

282
00:12:05,110 --> 00:12:06,930
That had to hurt!

283
00:12:09,940 --> 00:12:12,050
Hey, it's your Thanksgiving too.

284
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,640
Instead of watching football,

285
00:12:13,690 --> 00:12:14,780
you could help.

286
00:12:14,830 --> 00:12:15,970
We know.

287
00:12:17,490 --> 00:12:19,700
Rachel, you want to put the marshmallows

288
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:20,900
in concentric circles.

289
00:12:20,950 --> 00:12:21,870
No, Mon.

290
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:24,120
You want to put them in concentric circles.

291
00:12:24,170 --> 00:12:26,100
I want to do this.

292
00:12:35,590 --> 00:12:36,760
Every year.

293
00:12:40,590 --> 00:12:42,010
It's stuck!

294
00:12:43,470 --> 00:12:44,970
Step.

295
00:12:45,020 --> 00:12:46,480
How did it get on?

296
00:12:46,530 --> 00:12:49,280
I put it on to scare Chandler.

297
00:12:49,730 --> 00:12:51,150
Oh, my God!

298
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,450
Monica's going to totally freak out!

299
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,690
Plus, it smells really bad in here.

300
00:12:55,740 --> 00:12:57,330
Of course it smells bad.

301
00:12:57,380 --> 00:13:00,090
You have your head up a turkey's ass.

302
00:13:02,950 --> 00:13:03,950
Monica.

303
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:08,020
Did you get the turkey--?

304
00:13:08,070 --> 00:13:10,120
Oh, my God!

305
00:13:11,330 --> 00:13:12,530
Who is that?

306
00:13:12,810 --> 00:13:14,120
It's Joey.

307
00:13:15,330 --> 00:13:16,270
I got it!

308
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:17,950
If we win,

309
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,630
they have to get rid of the rooster.

310
00:13:19,680 --> 00:13:21,360
That's interesting!

311
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:24,240
If you win...

312
00:13:24,570 --> 00:13:26,020
...we give up the bird.

313
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:30,330
But if we win...

314
00:13:31,430 --> 00:13:32,890
...we get your apartment.

315
00:13:36,530 --> 00:13:37,890
- Deal! - What?

316
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,350
"What was Monica's nickname

317
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,070
when she was a hockey goalie?"

318
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,570
- Big Fat Goalie. - Correct!

319
00:13:45,290 --> 00:13:47,780
"Rachel claims it's her favorite movie."

320
00:13:47,830 --> 00:13:49,130
<i>Dangerous Liaisons</i>.

321
00:13:49,180 --> 00:13:50,850
Correct, "Her actual favorite movie is...?"

322
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:51,960
<i>Weekend at Bernie's</i>.

323
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:56,120
"Monica categorizes her towels.

324
00:13:56,170 --> 00:13:58,290
How many categories are there?"

325
00:13:58,340 --> 00:13:59,770
- Everyday use. - Fancy.

326
00:13:59,820 --> 00:14:01,420
- Guest. - Fancy guest.

327
00:14:01,470 --> 00:14:03,550
- Two seconds. - Eleven?

328
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:06,880
Eleven! Unbelievable! Eleven is correct.

329
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:10,100
"Chandler was how old

330
00:14:10,150 --> 00:14:11,760
when he first touched a girl's breast?"

331
00:14:11,810 --> 00:14:13,220
- 14? - No, 19.

332
00:14:13,270 --> 00:14:14,290
Thanks, man.

333
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:17,800
"Joey had an imaginary childhood friend.

334
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,160
- His name was...?" - Maurice!

335
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:20,610
Correct! "His profession was...?"

336
00:14:20,610 --> 00:14:22,020
Space cowboy!

337
00:14:23,940 --> 00:14:25,440
"What is Chandler Bing's job?"

338
00:14:31,070 --> 00:14:31,730
Ten seconds.

339
00:14:31,730 --> 00:14:32,920
You need this or you lose.

340
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:35,790
Something to do with transponding.

341
00:14:35,840 --> 00:14:38,580
He's a transpons...transponster!

342
00:14:39,380 --> 00:14:41,590
That's not even a word!

343
00:14:52,030 --> 00:14:54,710
You are mean boys

344
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:55,960
who are just being mean!

345
00:14:56,010 --> 00:14:57,580
Don't get mad!

346
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:59,470
No one forced you to raise the stakes.

347
00:14:59,520 --> 00:15:02,260
That is not true! She forced me!

348
00:15:02,310 --> 00:15:03,500
Hey, we would still be living here

349
00:15:03,550 --> 00:15:04,860
if you hadn't gotten the question wrong!

350
00:15:04,910 --> 00:15:07,440
It was a stupid, unfair question!

351
00:15:07,490 --> 00:15:09,200
Don't blame the questions!

352
00:15:09,330 --> 00:15:11,700
Stop yelling in our apartment!

353
00:15:11,750 --> 00:15:14,060
You are ruining moving day for us.

354
00:15:15,270 --> 00:15:16,470
Chandler!

355
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:22,540
I saw what you were doing in the window!

356
00:15:22,590 --> 00:15:24,620
I saw what you're doing to my sister!

357
00:15:24,670 --> 00:15:25,950
Get out here!

358
00:15:27,170 --> 00:15:28,940
Listen, we had a good run.

359
00:15:29,550 --> 00:15:31,680
What was it? Four, five months?

360
00:15:31,730 --> 00:15:32,730
I mean that's more

361
00:15:32,780 --> 00:15:33,970
than most people have in a lifetime.

362
00:15:34,020 --> 00:15:35,380
So, goodbye, take care, byebye.

363
00:15:37,740 --> 00:15:38,370
Hey, Ross.

364
00:15:38,420 --> 00:15:39,250
What's up, bro?

365
00:15:41,660 --> 00:15:45,750
What the hell are you doing?

366
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:46,850
What's going on?

367
00:15:46,900 --> 00:15:50,650
I think...I think Ross knows about me and Monica.

368
00:15:52,210 --> 00:15:54,280
Dude, he's right there.

369
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:58,270
I thought you were my best friend!

370
00:15:58,320 --> 00:15:59,870
This is my sister!

371
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:01,580
My best friend and my sister!

372
00:16:01,630 --> 00:16:03,230
I cannot believe this!

373
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:05,390
We're not just messing around.

374
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:06,740
I love her.

375
00:16:07,450 --> 00:16:08,900
I'm in love with her.

376
00:16:10,320 --> 00:16:11,140
I'm so sorry

377
00:16:11,190 --> 00:16:12,690
that you had to find out this way.

378
00:16:14,070 --> 00:16:15,590
I'm sorry, but it's true.

379
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:16,880
I love him too.

380
00:16:23,670 --> 00:16:26,530
My best friend and my sister!

381
00:16:29,190 --> 00:16:31,560
I cannot believe this!

382
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:34,790
This is the last box of your clothes.

383
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,170
I'm just gonna label it

384
00:16:36,220 --> 00:16:37,620
"What were you thinking?"

385
00:16:39,170 --> 00:16:41,600
I was gonna go across the hall

386
00:16:41,650 --> 00:16:43,210
and write that on Chandler.

387
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:48,570
Guys, I don't mean to make things worse, but...

388
00:16:48,620 --> 00:16:50,870
...l don't want to live with Rachel anymore.

389
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:51,740
-What? -What?

390
00:16:51,790 --> 00:16:53,840
You're so mean to each other.

391
00:16:53,890 --> 00:16:55,960
I don't wanna end up like that with Rachel.

392
00:16:56,010 --> 00:16:57,260
I still like you.

393
00:16:57,780 --> 00:17:00,260
That's fine because I'm not moving.

394
00:17:01,430 --> 00:17:02,930
Phoebe, you gotta take her.

395
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:06,070
You know, I know I said some bad stuff...

396
00:17:06,120 --> 00:17:08,390
...but Rachel has qualities

397
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:09,550
that make her a good roommate.

398
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:11,730
She gets tons of catalogs and she folds

399
00:17:11,780 --> 00:17:14,440
she folds down the pages of things she thinks I'd like.

400
00:17:15,060 --> 00:17:15,970
What else?

401
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:19,250
When I take a shower...

402
00:17:20,050 --> 00:17:21,920
...she leaves me notes on the mirror.

403
00:17:22,260 --> 00:17:24,020
I do. I do do that.

404
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:26,080
That's nice.

405
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:28,420
I like having things to read in the bathroom.

406
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:33,610
When I fall asleep on the couch...

407
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:36,480
...she covers me with a blanket.

408
00:17:37,090 --> 00:17:40,600
Well, you know, I don't want you to be cold.

409
00:17:44,210 --> 00:17:44,940
And when I told her

410
00:17:44,990 --> 00:17:46,690
that I was gonna move in with Chandler...

411
00:17:48,060 --> 00:17:49,990
...she was really supportive.

412
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,350
You were so great.

413
00:17:55,820 --> 00:17:58,240
You made it so easy.

414
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:02,650
And now you have to leave.

415
00:18:02,700 --> 00:18:05,230
And I have to live with a boy!

416
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:24,210
- She really left. - I know.

417
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:30,000
- Thank you. - No problem, roomie.

418
00:18:38,460 --> 00:18:40,690
- Can I ask you a question? - Sure.

419
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:43,100
What the hell is that dog doing here?

420
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:46,790
A little toast here. Ding, ding!

421
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:48,730
I know this isn't exactly

422
00:18:48,780 --> 00:18:50,640
the kind of Thanksgiving you planned...

423
00:18:50,690 --> 00:18:54,200
...but for me this has been really great.

424
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:56,260
You know, I think because

425
00:18:56,310 --> 00:18:58,290
it didn't involve divorce...

426
00:18:58,340 --> 00:18:59,720
...or projectile vomiting.

427
00:19:02,290 --> 00:19:03,360
Anyway, I think if

428
00:19:03,410 --> 00:19:04,300
you had gone to Vail...

429
00:19:04,350 --> 00:19:06,440
...or if you had been with your family,

430
00:19:06,490 --> 00:19:07,870
or if you didn't have...

431
00:19:08,860 --> 00:19:10,420
...syphilis and stuff...

432
00:19:12,470 --> 00:19:14,760
...we wouldn't be all together.

433
00:19:14,810 --> 00:19:17,040
So I guess what I'm trying to say is...

434
00:19:17,090 --> 00:19:19,210
...that I'm very thankful

435
00:19:19,260 --> 00:19:22,010
that all of your Thanksgivings sucked.

436
00:19:23,450 --> 00:19:26,470
- That's so sweet! - Thank you.

437
00:19:29,020 --> 00:19:31,200
Here's to a lousy Christmas!

438
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:32,810
And a crappy New Year!

439
00:19:32,860 --> 00:19:34,860
Hear, hear!

440
00:19:41,130 --> 00:19:42,170
You can't move.

441
00:19:42,220 --> 00:19:43,400
You just-- You just can't.

442
00:19:43,450 --> 00:19:44,240
Rachel's right.

443
00:19:44,290 --> 00:19:46,110
This is where you guys belong.

444
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:47,970
Yeah.You don't wanna live in Westchester.

445
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:49,770
That's the worst of the Chesters.

446
00:19:51,210 --> 00:19:51,890
You know,

447
00:19:51,940 --> 00:19:53,720
sometimes when I'm alone in my apartment,

448
00:19:53,770 --> 00:19:54,700
I look over here...

449
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:58,110
...and you guys are just having dinner...

450
00:19:58,590 --> 00:20:00,920
...or watching TV or something...

451
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:03,730
...but it makes me feel better.

452
00:20:03,780 --> 00:20:04,910
And now when I look over,

453
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:06,360
who am I gonna see?

454
00:20:06,410 --> 00:20:08,760
The Gottliebs? The Yangs?

455
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:11,980
They don't make me feel so good.

456
00:20:13,290 --> 00:20:15,830
Yeah. So don't move, okay?

457
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:17,330
Just stay here...

458
00:20:17,760 --> 00:20:19,380
...and maybe close your blinds at night.

459
00:20:19,380 --> 00:20:19,960
Hey.

460
00:20:26,370 --> 00:20:27,350
Hello?

461
00:20:30,820 --> 00:20:33,110
It's Nancy. They responded to our offer.

462
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:34,150
And?

463
00:20:37,150 --> 00:20:38,640
Okay. Thanks.

464
00:20:41,520 --> 00:20:42,430
They passed.

465
00:20:44,420 --> 00:20:46,980
They said they won't go a penny under the asking price.

466
00:20:47,290 --> 00:20:49,450
- We can't afford that. - I know.

467
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:53,620
Well, there you go.

468
00:20:58,540 --> 00:21:00,080
I'm really sorry, you guys.

469
00:21:00,130 --> 00:21:02,150
Yeah, I'm sorry too.

470
00:21:02,590 --> 00:21:04,800
I'm even more sorry that phone call didn't come...

471
00:21:04,850 --> 00:21:06,740
...before I told you about looking through the window.

472
00:21:08,220 --> 00:21:10,350
Yeah. Well, we're gonna let you be alone.

473
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,360
You gonna be okay?

474
00:21:11,410 --> 00:21:12,430
Yeah, we'll be okay.

475
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:13,620
Love you guys.

476
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:17,970
You know, I'm really sorry

477
00:21:18,020 --> 00:21:19,620
I wasn't more supportive before.

478
00:21:19,670 --> 00:21:20,250
That's okay.

479
00:21:20,300 --> 00:21:21,090
We understand.

480
00:21:21,140 --> 00:21:23,060
Yeah, and about this Nancy....

481
00:21:23,110 --> 00:21:24,950
If you're not sleeping with her, should l?

482
00:21:32,170 --> 00:21:34,760
I know there'll be other houses, but I just--

483
00:21:34,810 --> 00:21:37,250
- I love that one so much. - Yeah.

484
00:21:38,670 --> 00:21:40,540
Well, it's a good thing we got it then.

485
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:44,550
- What? - We got the house.

486
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:46,400
Oh, my God.

487
00:21:46,450 --> 00:21:48,170
I didn't wanna tell you in front of them.

488
00:21:48,220 --> 00:21:49,960
Oh my god, we got it?! We got the house?!

489
00:21:50,010 --> 00:21:51,370
We're getting a house!

490
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:58,650
- We're getting a house. - And a baby.

491
00:21:58,700 --> 00:22:00,000
We're growing up.

492
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:03,060
We sure are.

493
00:22:04,390 --> 00:22:05,390
- Who's gonna tell them? - Not it!

494
00:22:05,390 --> 00:22:07,020
Not it! Damn it!

495
00:22:12,230 --> 00:22:13,540
Rachel, this is yours.

496
00:22:14,130 --> 00:22:16,000
Why? What are these for?

497
00:22:16,050 --> 00:22:16,980
You'll see.

498
00:22:17,030 --> 00:22:18,830
All right, everybody open them.

499
00:22:21,340 --> 00:22:23,660
Wow, this is so beautiful!

500
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:26,650
These are the ones I was looking at in the store!

501
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:28,730
- I know. - Oh, I love this!

502
00:22:28,780 --> 00:22:30,480
A meatball sub!

503
00:22:31,370 --> 00:22:32,610
Thanks!

504
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:34,440
Seriously, guys, what's going on?

505
00:22:34,490 --> 00:22:35,560
What are these for?

506
00:22:35,610 --> 00:22:38,290
Well, I didn't know how to tell you before...

507
00:22:39,100 --> 00:22:41,010
- ...but we got the house. - Enjoy!

508
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:47,450
What did they say?

